3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper uses the Influence Function (IF) to measure the impact of training data on the final model, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper deals with improving the performance of machine learning models, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses differential privacy to protect sensitive information in machine learning models, which falls under the domain of information theory.
